1
00:00:02,035 --> 00:00:03,628
<i>Previously on</i> The Good Doctor:

2
00:00:03,704 --> 00:00:05,144
- We had the clinic at the hospital.

3
00:00:05,172 --> 00:00:08,199
Come back as president
and we'll reopen it.

4
00:00:08,575 --> 00:00:10,339
We need to go to HR and break up.

5
00:00:10,410 --> 00:00:12,845
I've accepted your explanation
and report.

6
00:00:12,913 --> 00:00:15,508
- Thank you.
- But I don't believe it.

7
00:00:16,183 --> 00:00:19,881
You don't get to lead surgeries
until fourth year. That will be changing.

8
00:00:19,953 --> 00:00:22,718
When the right surgery comes along,
it'll be yours.

9
00:00:23,357 --> 00:00:26,953
I want you to meet our new attending,
Doctor Marcus Andrews.

10
00:00:27,394 --> 00:00:28,862
Pleasure to meet you.

11
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:30,725
You had a date last night,
didn't you?

12
00:00:30,831 --> 00:00:34,359
It was hard, uncomfortable, unpleasant.

13
00:00:34,434 --> 00:00:39,270
And I have no idea if she was happy.
And I know I wasn't happy!

14
00:00:45,746 --> 00:00:48,841
- I don't like when you do that.
- I know.

15
00:00:48,916 --> 00:00:51,750
But I did it anyway,
because you need to snap out of it.

16
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:56,622
- The moping, it accomplishes nothing.
- I'm not moping, I'm eating.

17
00:00:56,723 --> 00:01:00,353
Which is the only thing you're doing
outside of your room now.

18
00:01:00,761 --> 00:01:03,595
You didn't even come out to tell me
to turn down the Talking Heads.

19
00:01:03,730 --> 00:01:07,292
- It didn't bother me.
- The walls were shaking.

20
00:01:07,601 --> 00:01:09,797
I'm surprised the cops
didn't show up.

21
00:01:12,239 --> 00:01:16,267
You like Carly. You need to get
back in the saddle,

22
00:01:16,376 --> 00:01:19,278
and luckily, you have
a totally awesome roomie

23
00:01:19,413 --> 00:01:23,509
- who's here to help you.
- I'm not going on any more dates.

24
00:01:23,750 --> 00:01:26,584
Shaun, everyone gets it.

25
00:01:26,653 --> 00:01:30,385
Dating is stressful,
but being alone is worse.

26
00:01:30,457 --> 00:01:34,827
I'm not alone. I have you.
I have Doctor Glassman.

27
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:37,955
Friends are great,
but everyone needs a special friend.

28
00:01:38,031 --> 00:01:39,192
I don't.

29
00:01:39,900 --> 00:01:42,836
- Shaun, I just...
- I'm not like everyone.

30
00:01:51,044 --> 00:01:54,947
No one is like everyone.
We're all unique.

31
00:01:56,183 --> 00:01:59,051
But we're also the same.

32
00:02:15,068 --> 00:02:16,434
I had rent control.

33
00:02:16,737 --> 00:02:19,673
The only way for them
to jack the rent is to get me out.

34
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:21,368
So they make up a reason.

35
00:02:21,475 --> 00:02:23,910
Said that I was playing my music
too loud.

36
00:02:25,045 --> 00:02:27,844
And all-night parties,
fighting with neighbors,

37
00:02:27,948 --> 00:02:31,043
wandering around the parking lot
without clothes?

38
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:32,244
I had a robe on!

39
00:02:32,352 --> 00:02:35,345
And I wasn't wandering,
I was trying to take the trash out,

40
00:02:35,455 --> 00:02:37,822
but they moved the damn bins.

41
00:02:38,558 --> 00:02:39,890
- It was windy.
- Mom,

42
00:02:39,993 --> 00:02:42,690
you are clearly off your
meds and drinking.

43
00:02:44,064 --> 00:02:46,499
Okay. Was.

44
00:02:47,501 --> 00:02:49,595
It was a temporary setback.

45
00:02:50,737 --> 00:02:53,536
Nobody's perfect,
but it is under control now.

46
00:02:53,607 --> 00:02:58,068
People under control don't show up
at 1 a.m. looking for a place to stay.

47
00:02:58,178 --> 00:03:02,377
I will be out of your hair
before you even know. Two weeks.

48
00:03:02,616 --> 00:03:04,244
- Three, tops.
- One!

49
00:03:04,584 --> 00:03:07,110
I don't have time
to babysit a grown woman.

50
00:03:07,220 --> 00:03:10,122
Three weeks until the end of the month.
You owe me that.

51
00:03:10,223 --> 00:03:12,522
No, I don't, actually. One week.

52
00:03:15,862 --> 00:03:17,455
- We need help!
- Male, 30s,

53
00:03:17,564 --> 00:03:20,090
10-centimeter laceration
to his left cheek.

54
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:23,932
Probable fractured temporal bone,
maxilla, definitely shattered mandible.

55
00:03:24,037 --> 00:03:25,630
What happened?
- Tried to stop a creeper

56
00:03:25,739 --> 00:03:26,638
from groping a woman.

57
00:03:26,740 --> 00:03:29,369
Bashed his skull in
with some skateboard.

58
00:03:29,443 --> 00:03:32,641
Wheels broke off
and the metal axle... did that.

59
00:03:32,746 --> 00:03:36,308
Okay, secure his airway, his mouth
is filling up with blood. Intubation cart.

60
00:03:36,416 --> 00:03:38,544
Through-and-through oral defect

61
00:03:38,618 --> 00:03:41,087
and the mandible is crushed.
We need hemostats.

62
00:03:41,555 --> 00:03:43,421
- The woman?
- She's fine.

63
00:03:43,657 --> 00:03:46,217
Cops arrived, Tased the dude,
took him away.

64
00:03:46,293 --> 00:03:48,387
Everybody's fine except the hero.

65
00:03:48,962 --> 00:03:50,897
We need to intubate through the neck.

66
00:03:50,964 --> 00:03:53,832
Betadine, scalpel, 6-0 tube
to place surgical cric.

67
00:04:05,178 --> 00:04:07,443
<i>Doctor Brigham to 435.</i>

68
00:04:07,681 --> 00:04:09,274
<i>Doctor Brigham to 435.</i>

69
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:12,750
Could you take this up to Lim's office?
I'm running late.

70
00:04:12,819 --> 00:04:13,819
No problem.

71
00:04:14,321 --> 00:04:15,584
Melendez is waiting.

72
00:04:15,655 --> 00:04:18,489
Sorry, had to help Kellan
with a biology project.

73
00:04:18,592 --> 00:04:21,084
- What's in the box?
- A Ducati throw pillow.

74
00:04:21,661 --> 00:04:25,291
- Think you can bribe Lim with a pillow?
- I'm not bribing her, I'm being nice.

75
00:04:25,365 --> 00:04:27,150
Starting a new
job in a new office.

76
00:04:27,174 --> 00:04:29,325
She'll decide who
gets first lead surgery.

77
00:04:29,436 --> 00:04:32,873
I don't think I can influence
her decision with a gift...

78
00:04:33,306 --> 00:04:36,640
but it never hurts to have
a relationship with your boss.

79
00:04:36,710 --> 00:04:38,372
And it's a damn cool pillow.

80
00:04:41,148 --> 00:04:42,148
Hey.

81
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:46,215
No signs of any post-op infection.

82
00:04:46,319 --> 00:04:48,515
There's also no sign
your surgery did any good.

83
00:04:48,622 --> 00:04:49,622
Tom!

84
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:54,390
- How often is he vomiting?
- After every feeding.

85
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:56,786
Okay. Shh...

86
00:04:58,632 --> 00:05:00,965
This is not the outcome we hoped for,

87
00:05:01,201 --> 00:05:04,194
but a pyloric stenosis
requires a cautious approach.

88
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:05,829
If we're too aggressive...

89
00:05:06,973 --> 00:05:09,636
It's okay, buddy.
I got you. There we go.

90
00:05:09,709 --> 00:05:10,904
Shh...

91
00:05:11,111 --> 00:05:13,603
- Hold on.
- Our baby is in pain.

92
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:16,479
He can't eat
and you don't have any clue why.

93
00:05:18,819 --> 00:05:22,381
I would be upset too if I were
in your position, but you're wrong.

94
00:05:22,689 --> 00:05:25,523
We need to conduct tests
to confirm, but I am confident

95
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:28,857
it's a matter of going back in
and making an adjustment.

96
00:05:29,729 --> 00:05:31,391
Your son's in good hands.

97
00:05:31,998 --> 00:05:33,125
Thank you.

98
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:36,898
- I'm sorry, I'm...
- A father who loves his son.

99
00:05:37,003 --> 00:05:39,268
You've got nothing to apologize for.

100
00:05:46,146 --> 00:05:47,512
That was impressive.

101
00:05:48,548 --> 00:05:50,346
Get an abdominal ultrasound
to confirm

102
00:05:50,417 --> 00:05:52,648
it's just an incomplete
pyloromyotomy.

103
00:05:56,423 --> 00:06:00,258
You're wasting your ass-kissing.
First surgery isn't his decision.

104
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:03,524
No, he's just the one sleeping
with the one making that decision.

105
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:11,970
- Pupils are equal and reactive.
- Do you know where you are?

106
00:06:14,708 --> 00:06:16,233
And do you know
how you ended up here?

107
00:06:19,312 --> 00:06:23,306
Josh, you have multiple fractures
in your cheek and jaw,

108
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:25,442
and a large piece of your cheek tissue,

109
00:06:25,552 --> 00:06:28,750
skin and underlying muscle was torn off.

110
00:06:29,089 --> 00:06:31,957
You're going to need extensive
reconstructive surgery

111
00:06:32,058 --> 00:06:33,651
to save your jaw function.

112
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:36,787
You need to read these consent forms,

113
00:06:36,963 --> 00:06:40,127
and if you have any questions,
write them on this pad.

114
00:06:40,734 --> 00:06:43,397
Was the woman on the subway
a friend of yours?

115
00:06:47,474 --> 00:06:48,474
<i>He's a fool.</i>

116
00:06:48,842 --> 00:06:51,744
Trying to prove how macho you are
can get you killed.

117
00:06:51,811 --> 00:06:54,610
Clamp the branch
of the inferior alveolar.

118
00:06:59,085 --> 00:07:03,455
So you would just stand by?
Let a woman get groped?

119
00:07:04,991 --> 00:07:07,984
Apply manual compression,
try and close the fracture gap.

120
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:11,360
Do you help every homeless addict
you see on the subway?

121
00:07:11,464 --> 00:07:14,093
- I don't.
- And neither does Browne.

122
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:16,636
Which is why she ought not get
so self-righteous.

123
00:07:16,937 --> 00:07:17,937
Yes.

124
00:07:18,004 --> 00:07:20,940
I help my patients
to the best of my ability

125
00:07:21,007 --> 00:07:25,377
because it's meaningful, and to me,
the downside is purely financial.

126
00:07:25,779 --> 00:07:27,475
For friends, I'll risk more,

127
00:07:27,547 --> 00:07:30,676
but the only people
I'm risking life and limb for

128
00:07:30,784 --> 00:07:32,013
are my family.

129
00:07:32,519 --> 00:07:35,751
Someone gropes my wife on the subway,
they're gonna get whupped.

130
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:39,282
This isn't gonna work.

131
00:07:39,759 --> 00:07:43,457
The mandibular ramus is too shattered
and I can't get stabilization.

132
00:07:43,530 --> 00:07:47,661
We can't do skin or muscle grafts
if we can't fix skeletal structures.

133
00:07:47,767 --> 00:07:50,828
Alloplastic augmentation
to bridge the gap?

134
00:07:50,904 --> 00:07:52,463
The span is too wide.

135
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,146
We're going to wire him shut.

136
00:08:03,917 --> 00:08:05,180
Wake him up.

137
00:08:05,785 --> 00:08:09,517
He should know he's never gonna talk
or eat solid food again.

138
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,829
Forever.

139
00:08:32,812 --> 00:08:34,110
Do you have questions?

140
00:08:38,251 --> 00:08:39,412
I'm sorry.

141
00:09:02,275 --> 00:09:04,244
The Cantrells want a new surgeon.

142
00:09:06,046 --> 00:09:08,538
What can you tell me
about the first surgery?

143
00:09:09,215 --> 00:09:10,649
Is this an M&M review?

144
00:09:11,951 --> 00:09:13,146
Not yet.

145
00:09:15,989 --> 00:09:19,585
Is it possible, you may have been
a little too aggressive?

146
00:09:19,959 --> 00:09:22,793
- Cut too deeply?
- Are you really asking me that?

147
00:09:22,896 --> 00:09:24,091
I need to know.

148
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,398
Definitely didn't go too deep.

149
00:09:30,103 --> 00:09:32,663
Great. We'll talk to the Cantrells.

150
00:09:35,175 --> 00:09:36,175
Audrey...

151
00:09:38,144 --> 00:09:39,510
is this weird for you?

152
00:09:41,915 --> 00:09:43,383
A little. You?

153
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:45,475
Trying not to let it be.

154
00:09:46,519 --> 00:09:48,511
Good. Me too.

155
00:09:53,693 --> 00:09:58,097
Hello. I'm here to pick up
artificial dermal regeneration templates.

156
00:09:58,431 --> 00:10:00,332
Let me get it. Hey, Shaun.

157
00:10:01,968 --> 00:10:03,766
I heard what happened to the guy.

158
00:10:03,837 --> 00:10:06,534
It sounds horrible.
Is he gonna be okay?

159
00:10:07,173 --> 00:10:10,405
He won't be able to eat
or speak normally ever again.

160
00:10:12,112 --> 00:10:13,671
- Thank you.
- Shaun.

161
00:10:15,915 --> 00:10:17,781
You seem a bit uncomfortable.

162
00:10:18,985 --> 00:10:23,821
If it has anything to do with our date,
I want you to know, I had a good time...

163
00:10:24,190 --> 00:10:25,852
and hope we can do it again.

164
00:10:31,231 --> 00:10:34,133
I had... a horrible time...

165
00:10:35,201 --> 00:10:39,002
and... don't want to do that ever again.

166
00:10:51,484 --> 00:10:53,043
Extensive swelling.

167
00:10:53,153 --> 00:10:55,645
But within the acceptable range
of post-op edema.

168
00:10:55,722 --> 00:10:57,418
The very top of the range.

169
00:10:57,824 --> 00:11:00,225
I think maybe Melendez
did go too deep,

170
00:11:00,393 --> 00:11:02,157
- injured the pylorus.
- Well?

171
00:11:03,463 --> 00:11:06,831
The swelling is within the acceptable
range for a post-op edema.

172
00:11:08,902 --> 00:11:10,837
Got your muffins. Delicious.

173
00:11:10,904 --> 00:11:12,839
- I'm glad you liked them.
- I did.

174
00:11:12,906 --> 00:11:15,569
Just surprised you thought
I could be bought.

175
00:11:16,109 --> 00:11:18,349
We're not trying to buy you off
with muffins or a pillow.

176
00:11:18,678 --> 00:11:20,169
Someone got me a pillow?

177
00:11:22,749 --> 00:11:25,685
No. I wanted to show
my support for your promotion.

178
00:11:26,486 --> 00:11:30,685
You're all gonna lead surgeries.
Doesn't matter who does anything first.

179
00:11:30,757 --> 00:11:33,750
The only thing that matters
is that you do it right.

180
00:11:37,931 --> 00:11:39,923
So, what was in the box?

181
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:43,060
Sample marketing pamphlets.
My buddy owns a print shop

182
00:11:43,136 --> 00:11:45,230
and asked me to give Lim samples.

183
00:11:45,905 --> 00:11:47,203
Well played.

184
00:11:47,273 --> 00:11:49,799
But it's all moot anyway,
it doesn't matter who goes first.

185
00:11:50,443 --> 00:11:51,604
Right.

186
00:11:52,378 --> 00:11:54,904
So I'm clear, that "right" was sarcastic?

187
00:11:55,014 --> 00:11:56,038
Right.

188
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:04,717
Hey.

189
00:12:04,791 --> 00:12:08,284
Since when does the president
need to stock his own shelves?

190
00:12:08,394 --> 00:12:11,387
When it's a free clinic
and want it done right.

191
00:12:13,032 --> 00:12:14,295
Thank you.

192
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,892
Have you ever had sex in the office?

193
00:12:16,970 --> 00:12:20,805
I'm not gonna answer that.
First, it's embarrassing if I say yes.

194
00:12:21,140 --> 00:12:24,770
And it's even more embarrassing
if I say no. I take the fifth.

195
00:12:24,844 --> 00:12:28,303
If we're gonna get
married, I need to know all your naughty...

196
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:31,350
I brought us lunch.
I know what you each like.

197
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:37,049
Doctor Melendez
is not just our best surgeon,

198
00:12:37,123 --> 00:12:38,955
he's one of the tops in the country.

199
00:12:39,058 --> 00:12:41,789
With the expertise to know
the best way to avoid

200
00:12:41,861 --> 00:12:46,094
a truly bad outcome in this procedure
is to err on the side of caution.

201
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:49,633
- We hear all that.
- We do.

202
00:12:49,702 --> 00:12:53,503
And we appreciate you
taking time to explain everything.

203
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:58,570
But we would just
be more comfortable

204
00:12:58,645 --> 00:13:00,773
having someone else take over.

205
00:13:00,847 --> 00:13:02,042
You do understand.

206
00:13:03,182 --> 00:13:04,182
Of course.

207
00:13:05,451 --> 00:13:09,218
I assume you'd be okay if I performed
Braden's second surgery?

208
00:13:10,723 --> 00:13:13,158
The chief of the department? Uh...

209
00:13:13,226 --> 00:13:15,821
Absolutely. Thank you, doctor.

210
00:13:15,895 --> 00:13:16,954
Of course.

211
00:13:22,902 --> 00:13:24,530
Nobody likes dating.

212
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:27,539
It's awkward and uncomfortable
and it's expensive.

213
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:30,667
Ah. That's why you proposed
after two dates, to save money.

214
00:13:30,743 --> 00:13:33,042
I proposed after two dates
because after one,

215
00:13:33,146 --> 00:13:35,843
I realized how much
I loved being around you.

216
00:13:36,149 --> 00:13:38,209
And how much fun
we'd have together.

217
00:13:38,318 --> 00:13:41,413
He's right, Shaun.
Because the fun can be so fun.

218
00:13:43,323 --> 00:13:45,656
That didn't happen to me.

219
00:13:49,762 --> 00:13:51,424
I have to go to surgery.

220
00:13:52,065 --> 00:13:55,194
Shaun, whenever you're ready,
you'll try again.

221
00:14:00,940 --> 00:14:03,068
- What?
- Whenever he's ready?

222
00:14:03,176 --> 00:14:04,940
He's gotta go at his own pace.

223
00:14:05,378 --> 00:14:08,405
- He needs to be pushed.
- I'm not gonna push him.

224
00:14:08,514 --> 00:14:10,540
A man doesn't push another man
into a date.

225
00:14:10,650 --> 00:14:13,347
- He pushed you.
- Shaun doesn't know any better.

226
00:14:13,419 --> 00:14:15,354
If you want him to find love,

227
00:14:15,421 --> 00:14:17,856
he literally needs to be
pushed into it.

228
00:14:17,924 --> 00:14:19,017
Literally?

229
00:14:19,592 --> 00:14:21,288
Shaun's not like other men.

230
00:14:21,594 --> 00:14:23,460
He easily admits he's wrong?

231
00:14:23,930 --> 00:14:26,297
He easily changes course?

232
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:31,100
If you don't talk to him,
is anything gonna change?

233
00:14:34,907 --> 00:14:37,172
No good deed goes unpunished.

234
00:14:37,243 --> 00:14:39,610
Why does it always work out that way?

235
00:14:39,712 --> 00:14:43,376
It doesn't.
Most good deeds get rewarded.

236
00:14:44,083 --> 00:14:45,661
What do you base that on,
Murphy?

237
00:14:45,685 --> 00:14:48,553
Certainly not the news or the Forbes 500.

238
00:14:48,621 --> 00:14:51,785
- Or the Bible.
- I base it on neuroscience.

239
00:14:51,891 --> 00:14:55,328
Bad outcomes just implant deeper
in our cerebral cortex.

240
00:14:55,461 --> 00:14:59,831
So evolution agrees with me,
our brains encourage us to be selfish.

241
00:14:59,932 --> 00:15:05,701
Yes, which makes it strange
that people keep being unselfish.

242
00:15:05,772 --> 00:15:06,772
You were.

243
00:15:09,342 --> 00:15:12,608
You saved my job,
and now you're an attending

244
