00:32:34,186 --> 00:32:36,985
We only know about the second
condition because of the first surgery.

490
00:32:37,289 --> 00:32:41,351
Treatment protocol's a barium enema,
but not for someone Braden's age.

491
00:32:41,860 --> 00:32:45,126
- An air enema might work.
- Unless the intestine's torn.

492
00:32:46,665 --> 00:32:49,499
Morgan, reposition the scope
to get a better look

493
00:32:49,568 --> 00:32:52,800
at the intestinal wall
around the intussusception site.

494
00:32:55,707 --> 00:32:57,642
Too much swelling and edema
to be sure.

495
00:32:57,709 --> 00:33:00,178
With the risk of infection,
we don't have time to find out.

496
00:33:00,278 --> 00:33:03,043
- You're gonna have to open him up.
- You should.

497
00:33:03,782 --> 00:33:05,683
The Cantrells made their wishes clear.

498
00:33:05,784 --> 00:33:09,186
Well, that's when I made them think
you'd erred. Which you did not.

499
00:33:09,321 --> 00:33:11,813
Not on the side of caution, not at all.

500
00:33:13,024 --> 00:33:14,356
We do the surgery together.

501
00:33:15,427 --> 00:33:17,589
- Who's the lead?
- I think you know.

502
00:33:18,396 --> 00:33:20,194
- Pulling rank?
- Absolutely.

503
00:33:20,899 --> 00:33:23,664
As chief of surgery, I designate you.

504
00:33:24,569 --> 00:33:27,505
It's like a puzzle.
You secure the artery,

505
00:33:27,572 --> 00:33:30,906
then the vessel
just won't quite stretch to the vein.

506
00:33:31,009 --> 00:33:34,241
You could mobilize
the recipient vessel.

507
00:33:35,580 --> 00:33:37,048
Repeat that, Doctor Browne.

508
00:33:37,115 --> 00:33:40,415
Mobilize the recipient vessel
to create more slack.

509
00:33:45,323 --> 00:33:48,919
- You saw Carly again. How was it?
- Inconvenient.

510
00:33:49,594 --> 00:33:51,620
But despite her intrusion,

511
00:33:51,730 --> 00:33:54,359
I was still able to concentrate
on medicine.

512
00:33:54,432 --> 00:33:56,401
It wasn't an intrusion,
that was a date.

513
00:33:56,468 --> 00:33:57,902
It was walking.

514
00:33:58,236 --> 00:34:02,367
Walking with someone you like
who likes you too is a non-date date.

515
00:34:02,541 --> 00:34:04,373
Some of the best dates I've had

516
00:34:04,442 --> 00:34:07,844
did not involve flowers
and restaurant reservations, just

517
00:34:08,547 --> 00:34:11,244
sharing a bag of chips
and sitting on a couch.

518
00:34:13,051 --> 00:34:15,486
Secured. Remove clamps.

519
00:34:18,223 --> 00:34:20,283
Blood flow to and from graft.

520
00:34:20,392 --> 00:34:22,258
Let's move on
to the pectoralis flap.

521
00:34:23,595 --> 00:34:26,895
- Blood pressure's dropping.
- Okay, heart rate is up.

522
00:34:26,965 --> 00:34:28,661
Push IV fluids, give epinephrine

523
00:34:28,733 --> 00:34:30,133
one milligram, then start a drip.

524
00:34:31,603 --> 00:34:34,505
- There's intestinal wall perforation.
- Repairable?

525
00:34:36,274 --> 00:34:38,004
There's too much tissue damage.

526
00:34:38,376 --> 00:34:40,572
- Infection?
- No sign of peritonitis,

527
00:34:40,645 --> 00:34:43,137
but we'll need to remove
this section of bowel.

528
00:34:46,952 --> 00:34:48,682
- He's tachy.
- Hypotensive.

529
00:34:48,787 --> 00:34:51,086
Push vasopressors and antibiotics.

530
00:34:51,590 --> 00:34:54,788
Check an i-STAT hematocrit,
ABG. Give two units PRBCs.

531
00:34:54,893 --> 00:34:56,862
I don't see any major bleeding.

532
00:34:56,928 --> 00:34:59,159
Push more fluids,
start an inotrope.

533
00:34:59,264 --> 00:35:01,893
Check all vessels we worked
on for clots with the doppler.

534
00:35:01,967 --> 00:35:03,128
Okay.

535
00:35:09,341 --> 00:35:11,207
Large clot in the carotid.

536
00:35:11,309 --> 00:35:14,507
Clamps back on,
performing carotid arteriotomy.

537
00:35:14,646 --> 00:35:17,616
Will try to aspirate out the clot.
Standby with heparin.

538
00:35:24,322 --> 00:35:25,790
Carotid clot removed.

539
00:35:31,796 --> 00:35:33,458
EEG looking good.

540
00:35:34,466 --> 00:35:36,833
Resuming pectoralis flap dissection.

541
00:35:38,737 --> 00:35:40,035
Good work, everybody.

542
00:36:15,674 --> 00:36:17,336
Go ahead, say something.

543
00:36:18,109 --> 00:36:21,238
Yeah, you can talk.
Maybe not too much at first,

544
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:23,512
give the jaw a chance to heal.

545
00:36:26,751 --> 00:36:28,117
Thank you.

546
00:36:32,557 --> 00:36:34,685
On behalf of all of us,
you're very welcome.

547
00:36:36,294 --> 00:36:39,526
The woman who was being accosted
when you intervened is here.

548
00:36:40,298 --> 00:36:41,391
Is she all right?

549
00:36:41,499 --> 00:36:45,266
She's not here as a patient,
she's been waiting to see you.

550
00:36:46,004 --> 00:36:47,004
Okay?

551
00:36:56,581 --> 00:36:57,581
Hello.

552
00:36:58,283 --> 00:36:59,283
Hey.

553
00:37:00,385 --> 00:37:02,911
I am so sorry this happened.

554
00:37:03,755 --> 00:37:04,755
Me too.

555
00:37:06,391 --> 00:37:07,450
You look...

556
00:37:07,926 --> 00:37:10,589
When the swelling goes down,
he'll look a lot better.

557
00:37:11,463 --> 00:37:14,729
It's okay.
My face was never my fortune.

558
00:37:17,902 --> 00:37:19,097
What made you do it?

559
00:37:20,772 --> 00:37:22,035
Why did you step in?

560
00:37:24,843 --> 00:37:25,936
I don't know.

561
00:37:28,113 --> 00:37:29,445
You needed help.

562
00:37:37,322 --> 00:37:38,915
Olivia, by the way.

563
00:37:39,691 --> 00:37:42,627
- Josh.
- We'll let you two get acquainted.

564
00:37:50,068 --> 00:37:53,095
It didn't matter who got
the first lead surgery to me,

565
00:37:53,171 --> 00:37:55,834
but it's recently been brought
to my attention

566
00:37:55,940 --> 00:37:58,432
how much it might mean
to some of you.

567
00:37:58,643 --> 00:38:01,340
Seems I'd forgotten
how important this decision is

568
00:38:01,446 --> 00:38:03,711
when you've been dreaming
about it for years.

569
00:38:03,815 --> 00:38:05,545
You're all excellent candidates,

570
00:38:05,650 --> 00:38:08,586
each deserving
and will all get your turn.

571
00:38:09,854 --> 00:38:12,016
- Starting with Doctor Browne.
- Yes!

572
00:38:13,491 --> 00:38:14,550
Thank you.

573
00:38:22,100 --> 00:38:24,126
- Congratulations.
- Thanks.

574
00:38:26,337 --> 00:38:29,535
- What the hell was that?
- I was happy for a colleague.

575
00:38:29,641 --> 00:38:33,840
You weren't campaigning for you to win,
you were campaigning for me to lose.

576
00:38:33,912 --> 00:38:36,177
Do you dislike me that much?

577
00:38:36,848 --> 00:38:39,818
I just wouldn't want you
supervising me as chief resident.

578
00:38:39,884 --> 00:38:41,876
You'd be a nightmare of a boss.

579
00:38:50,695 --> 00:38:51,924
Shaun...

580
00:38:54,699 --> 00:38:56,861
Doctor Lim thought my motives
for fighting this hard

581
00:38:56,935 --> 00:38:58,836
for this patient were miscalculated.

582
00:39:01,206 --> 00:39:02,206
She was right.

583
00:39:02,874 --> 00:39:04,934
We shouldn't have saved his face?

584
00:39:05,443 --> 00:39:08,277
We have limited resources
and we're even more limited

585
00:39:08,379 --> 00:39:10,848
in our personal capacity
to determine who is deserving,

586
00:39:10,915 --> 00:39:13,384
so we make a choice
to treat everyone the same.

587
00:39:13,952 --> 00:39:16,922
So why did you treat
this patient differently?

588
00:39:17,755 --> 00:39:19,155
Because I was angry.

589
00:39:20,558 --> 00:39:22,959
I made a sacrifice to save you.

590
00:39:24,262 --> 00:39:27,255
I lost my job,
I took a substantial demotion

591
00:39:27,365 --> 00:39:31,393
and I thought I was a fool.
The cost was way too high.

592
00:39:32,437 --> 00:39:36,238
I resented you
and I, kind of, resented the universe.

593
00:39:39,677 --> 00:39:40,701
But today...

594
00:39:42,213 --> 00:39:44,273
you made me proud of my sacrifice.

595
00:39:46,484 --> 00:39:47,484
Thank you.

596
00:39:51,089 --> 00:39:52,284
You're welcome.

597
00:39:54,792 --> 00:39:59,230
Very few things that are worthwhile in life
come without a cost, Shaun.

598
00:40:20,318 --> 00:40:21,318
This is tricky.

599
00:40:22,220 --> 00:40:24,849
I feel like we were just tested
and both of us failed.

600
00:40:27,292 --> 00:40:30,421
But... we'll get better at this.

601
00:40:43,875 --> 00:40:46,970
Hey, honey. I'll make you a plate
and you can take it to your room.

602
00:40:48,112 --> 00:40:49,112
Thanks.

603
00:40:50,782 --> 00:40:54,048
I saw three more apartments today.
One was kind of nice,

604
00:40:54,152 --> 00:40:57,145
but it's not ready
until a week from this Tuesday,

605
00:40:57,288 --> 00:41:00,383
which puts me
over your deadline by three days.

606
00:41:02,961 --> 00:41:03,985
No.

607
00:41:05,863 --> 00:41:08,264
- Three days, come on.
- You can stay here.

608
00:41:09,067 --> 00:41:12,902
For a little while,
until you're a bit better.

609
00:41:13,571 --> 00:41:16,006
But you have to stay on your meds.

610
00:41:16,074 --> 00:41:19,704
Keep away from other drugs and alcohol,
I'm testing your urine every two days.

611
00:41:19,811 --> 00:41:22,576
Don't miss any appointments
with Doctor Donovan.

612
00:41:23,581 --> 00:41:25,015
Can you live with that?

613
00:41:40,999 --> 00:41:42,433
Do you have a couch?

614
00:41:51,676 --> 00:41:54,077
<i>♪ You held the balance of the time ♪</i>

615
00:41:54,178 --> 00:41:57,671
<i>♪ That only blindly I could read you ♪</i>

616
00:41:57,749 --> 00:42:00,116
<i>♪ But I could read you ♪</i>

617
00:42:01,085 --> 00:42:03,247
<i>♪ It's like you told me ♪</i>

618
00:42:03,354 --> 00:42:05,619
<i>♪ Go forward slowly ♪</i>

619
00:42:05,723 --> 00:42:08,921
<i>♪ It's not a race to the end ♪</i>

620
00:42:10,528 --> 00:42:12,895
<i>♪ Well, you look like yourself ♪</i>

621
00:42:15,133 --> 00:42:18,695
<i>♪ Only it ain't on the surface ♪</i>

622
00:42:19,971 --> 00:42:21,906
<i>♪ Well, you talk like yourself ♪</i>

623
00:42:21,973 --> 00:42:24,568
<i>♪ No, I hear someone else, though ♪</i>

624
00:42:24,642 --> 00:42:27,976
<i>♪ Now you're making me nervous ♪♪</i>
